31/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The European Commission progress report scheduled for release next week commends Turkey for legal reforms taken in an effort to bring legislation closer to that of EU, but criticises deficiencies in implementation, said Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Thursday (30 October). He acknowledged that implementation is incomplete but said that will change now that a reform monitoring committee has been established.
In other news Thursday, Economy Minister Ali Babacan announced that Turkey's currency, the lira, would be denominated on 1 January 2005. Six zeros will be erased from its value. Babacan is in New York, attending a UN General Assembly conference on development financing. (NTV, TRT 2, Anadolu Agency, NTV - 30/10/03)
